# OT Sentinel — Known Modbus Masters CDB List
# ==========================================
# Format: IP_ADDRESS:Description
#
# This list tracks ALL Modbus master IPs ever observed on the network.
# Used by rule 200003 (OT-SENTINEL-MOD-003) to detect new/rogue masters.
#
# Tuning strategy for MOD-003:
# 1. Start with this file EMPTY (delete all entries below)
# 2. Deploy rule 200003 — every Modbus IP will alert once
# 3. For each alert, investigate: is this IP legitimate?
# 4. If legitimate, ADD it to this list
# 5. After 1-2 weeks, all legitimate masters are listed
# 6. Future alerts represent true rogue devices
#
# Deployment: Copy to /var/ossec/etc/lists/ and add to ossec.conf:
#   <list>etc/lists/known_modbus_masters</list>

